@startuml nav_route_class_to_lane_model_valid_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Nav Route Class To Lane Model Valid Signal Flow\n(NAV route class + path readiness -> FCAM lane model validity)

participant "NAV / path inputs" as NavCtx #F4F7FB
participant "FCAM\nlane-model owner" as FCAM #E8F7E8
participant "Camera/lane state bus" as LaneBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / pilot consumers" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Route And Path Inputs ==

NavCtx -> FCAM : gNavRouteClass\nnavInputStale\npathReady
FCAM -> FCAM : if pathReady == 0\nthen navRouteClass = 0
FCAM -> FCAM : laneModelValid =\n(pathReady == 1 and navInputStale == 0 and navRouteClass in {2,3}) ? 1 : 0
note right of FCAM
Representative gating inputs
- navRouteClass
- navInputStale
- pathReady
end note

== Lane Model Publish ==

FCAM -> LaneBus : frmFcamInputMsg\nLaneModelValid / Confidence / route-class context
note right of FCAM
Representative outputs
- LaneModelValid
- Confidence
- route-class-informed lane status
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

LaneBus -> Obs : lane-model readback /\nhighway pilot consumers

note over NavCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. NAV route class and path freshness reach FCAM
2. FCAM validates whether lane model is usable
3. LaneModelValid is published on the FCAM state path
4. Downstream pilot/observer consumers see lane readiness
end note

@enduml
